  "text": "NK lytic proteins and FOXP3 levels was assessed via intracellular staining [CITATION_1] . Isolated PBMCs (1×10 7 cells/ml) were labelled with fluorochrome-conjugated monoclonal antibodies CD56, CD16 and CD3; CD25, CD127 and CD4 (BD Pharmingen, San Diego, CA) for the seclusion of NK cells and Tregs from whole blood samples. Samples were then fixed and permeablised with BD Cytofix (BD Pharmingen, San Diego, CA) and diluted perm wash buffer (BD Pharmingen, San Diego, CA) respectively. Cells were then stained with perforin, granzyme A (GZA), granzyme B (GZB) or FOXP3 (BD Pharmingen, San Diego, CA) and analysed on the flow cytometer.",
